[New human cases of H7N9 continue to be reported from China as well as those associated with travel from affected regions in China such as the one in Macau. Continued surveillance is mandated in the affected regions to detect animal reservoirs of the virus and institute preventive and control measures. - Mod.UBA

Maps of China can be seen at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/txu-pclmaps-oclc-747676570-china_admin-2011.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4763810,155. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
